Aviano Air Base.label: Aviano Air Base
Aviano Air Base.description: Aviano Air Base is a NATO base in northeastern Italy, in the Friuli-Venezia Giulia region. It is located in the Aviano municipality, at the foot of the Carnic Pre-Alps, or Southern Carnic Alps, about 15 kilometers from Pordenone. Wikipedia

Dyess Air Force Base.label: Dyess Air Force Base
Dyess Air Force Base.description:
Dyess Air Force Base is a United States Air Force base located approximately 7 miles southwest of Abilene, Texas.
The host unit at Dyess is the 7th Bomb Wing assigned to the Air Combat Command Twelfth Air Force. Wikipedia

Edwards Air Force Base.label: Edwards Air Force Base
Edwards Air Force Base.description: Edwards Air Force Base is a United States Air Force base located approximately 22 miles northeast of Lancaster, California. Wikipedia

Ellsworth Air Force Base.label: Ellsworth Air Force Base
Ellsworth Air Force Base.description: Ellsworth Air Force Base is a United States Air Force base located approximately 10 miles northeast of Rapid City, South Dakota just north of Box Elder, South Dakota. Wikipedia

Fort Bragg.label: Fort Bragg
Fort Bragg.description: Fort Bragg is a large United States Army installation, located in Cumberland, Hoke, Harnett and Moore counties, North Carolina, mostly in Fayetteville but also partly in the town of Spring Lake. Wikipedia

Fort Drum.label: Fort Drum
Fort Drum.description:
Fort Drum is a census-designated place and U.S. Army military reservation in Jefferson County, New York, United States. The population was 12,955 at the 2010 census. It is home to the 10th Mountain Division.
Fort Drum consists of 107,265 acres. Wikipedia

Hill Air Force Base.label: Hill Air Force Base
Hill Air Force Base.description: Hill Air Force Base is a major U.S. Air Force base located in northern Utah, just south of the city of Ogden, and near the towns of Clearfield, Riverdale, Roy, Sunset, and Layton. It is about 30 miles north of Salt Lake City. Wikipedia

Kirtland Air Force Base.label: Kirtland Air Force Base
Kirtland Air Force Base.description: Kirtland Air Force Base is a United States Air Force base located in the southeast quadrant of the Albuquerque, New Mexico urban area, adjacent to the Albuquerque International Sunport. Wikipedia

Luke Air Force Base.label: Luke Air Force Base
Luke Air Force Base.description: Luke Air Force Base is a United States Air Force base located seven miles west of the central business district of Glendale, in Maricopa County, Arizona, United States. It is also about 15 miles west of Phoenix, Arizona. Wikipedia

MacDill Air Force Base.label: MacDill Air Force Base
MacDill Air Force Base.description: MacDill Air Force Base is an active United States Air Force base located approximately 6.4 km south-southwest of downtown Tampa, Florida. Wikipedia

Malmstrom Air Force Base.label: Malmstrom Air Force Base
Malmstrom Air Force Base.description: Malmstrom Air Force Base is a United States Air Force base and census-designated place in Great Falls, Cascade County, Montana, United States. It was named in honor of World War II POW Colonel Einar Axel Malmstrom. Wikipedia

Maxwell Air Force Base.label: Maxwell Air Force Base
Maxwell Air Force Base.description: Maxwell Air Force Base, officially known as Maxwell-Gunter Air Force Base, is a United States Air Force installation under the Air Education and Training Command. The installation is located in Montgomery, Alabama, US. Wikipedia

Moody Air Force Base.label: Moody Air Force Base
Moody Air Force Base.description: Moody Air Force Base is a United States Air Force installation located in Lowndes County and Lanier County, about 9 miles northeast of Valdosta, Georgia, United States. Wikipedia

Nellis Air Force Base.label: Nellis Air Force Base
Nellis Air Force Base.description: Nellis Air Force Base is a southern Nevada installation with military schools and more squadrons than any other USAF base. Wikipedia

Patrick Air Force Base.label: Patrick Air Force Base
Patrick Air Force Base.description: Patrick Air Force Base is a United States Air Force Base located between Satellite Beach and Cocoa Beach, in Brevard County, Florida, United States. It was named in honor of Major General Mason Patrick. Wikipedia

Ramat David Airbase.label: Ramat David Airbase
Ramat David Airbase.description: Ramat David Israeli Air Force Base is one of three principal airbases of the Israeli Air Force, located southeast of Haifa, close to kibbutz Ramat David and Megiddo in the Jezreel Valley. Wikipedia

Ramstein Air Base.label: Ramstein Air Base
Ramstein Air Base.description: Ramstein Air Base is a United States Air Force base in Rhineland-Palatinate, a state of Germany. It serves as headquarters for the U.S. Air Forces in Europe and is also a North Atlantic Treaty Organization installation. Wikipedia

Seymour Johnson Air Force Base.label: Seymour Johnson Air Force Base
Seymour Johnson Air Force Base.description: Seymour Johnson Air Force Base is a United States Air Force base located to the southeast of Goldsboro, North Carolina. Wikipedia

Whiteman Air Force Base.label: Whiteman Air Force Base
Whiteman Air Force Base.description: Whiteman Air Force Base is a United States Air Force base located approximately 2 miles south of Knob Noster, Missouri; 70 miles east-southeast of Kansas City, Missouri. Wikipedia

Wolf's Lair.label: Wolf's Lair
Wolf's Lair.description: Wolf's Lair was Adolf Hitler's first Eastern Front military headquarters in World War II. The complex, which would become one of several Führerhauptquartiere located in various parts of occupied Europe, ... Wikipedia

Barcaldine Castle.label: Barcaldine Castle
Barcaldine Castle.description: Barcaldine Castle is a 17th-century tower house castle located at Barcaldine near Oban, Scotland. The castle was built by Sir Duncan Campbell, of Glenorchy, between 1601 and 1609. Wikipedia

Braemar Castle.label: Braemar Castle
Braemar Castle.description: Braemar Castle is situated near the village of Braemar in Aberdeenshire, Scotland. It is a possession of the chief of Clan Farquharson and is leased to a local charitable foundation. It is open to the public. Wikipedia

Brodick Castle.label: Brodick Castle
Brodick Castle.description: Brodick Castle is a castle situated outside the port of Brodick on the Isle of Arran, an island in the Firth of Clyde, Scotland. It was previously a seat of the Dukes of Hamilton, but is now owned by the National Trust for Scotland. Wikipedia

Camp David.label: Camp David
Camp David.description: Camp David is the country retreat of the President of the United States. It is located in wooded hills about 62 miles north-northwest of Washington, D.C., in Catoctin Mountain Park near Thurmont, Maryland. Wikipedia

Castel Nuovo.label: Castel Nuovo
Castel Nuovo.description: Castel Nuovo, often called Maschio Angioino, is a medieval castle in the city of Naples, southern Italy. It is the main symbol of the architecture of the city, and has been expanded or renovated several times since it was first begun in 1279. Wikipedia

Castello di Lunghezza.label: Castello di Lunghezza
Castello di Lunghezza.description: The Castello di Lunghezza is a medieval fortification situated roughly 20 kilometers east of Rome, Italy. It lies in Municipio VIII of Rome, and probably sits on the site of the ancient town of Collatia. Wikipedia
Castello di Lunghezza.Address: Via della Tenuta del Cavaliere, 230, 00010 Lunghezza Roma, Italy

Ertholmene.label: Ertholmene
Ertholmene.description: Ertholmene, generally called Christiansø, is a small archipelago situated approximately 18 km northeast of Bornholm in the Baltic Sea. Its permanent population is 90 and its area is 39 hectares. Wikipedia

Glamis Castle.label: Glamis Castle
Glamis Castle.description: Glamis Castle is situated beside the village of Glamis in Angus, Scotland. It is the home of the Earl and Countess of Strathmore and Kinghorne, and is open to the public. Wikipedia

Huntly Castle.label: Huntly Castle
Huntly Castle.description: Huntly Castle is a ruined castle in Huntly in Aberdeenshire, Scotland. It was the ancestral home of the chief of Clan Gordon, Earl of Huntly. Wikipedia

Hurst Castle.label: Hurst Castle
Hurst Castle.description: Hurst Castle on the south coast of England is one of Henry VIII's Device Forts, built at the end of a long shingle spit at the west end of the Solent to guard the approaches to Southampton. Wikipedia

Leslie Castle.label: Castle Leslie
Leslie Castle.description: Castle Leslie, home to an Irish branch of Clan Leslie and located on the 4 km², Castle Leslie is both the name of a historic Country House and 1,000-acre Estate adjacent to the village of Glaslough, ... Wikipedia

Lunt Roman Fort.label: Lunt Roman Fort
Lunt Roman Fort.description: The Lunt Roman Fort is the archaeological site of a Roman fort, of unknown name, in the Roman province of Britannia. It is open to the public and located in the village of Baginton outside Coventry, Warwickshire. Wikipedia

Pendennis Castle.label: Pendennis Castle
Pendennis Castle.description: Pendennis Castle is one of Henry VIII's Device Forts, or Henrician castle, in the English county of Cornwall. It was built between 1539 - 1545 for King Henry VIII to guard the entrance to the River Fal on its west bank, near Falmouth. Wikipedia

Pitsligo Castle.label: Pitsligo Castle
Pitsligo Castle.description: Pitsligo Castle is a ruined castle half a mile east of Rosehearty, Aberdeenshire, Scotland. It was described by W. Douglas Simpson as one of the nine castles of the Knuckle, referring to the rocky headland of north-east Aberdeenshire. Wikipedia

RAF Holmpton.label: RAF Holmpton
RAF Holmpton.description: RAF Holmpton is a former Cold War era nuclear bunker that was built in the 1950s as an early warning radar station. Wikipedia

Portland Castle.label: Portland Castle
Portland Castle.description: Portland Castle is one of the Device Forts, also known as Henrician Castles, built in 1539 by Henry VIII on the Isle of Portland to guard the natural Portland anchorage known as the Portland Roads. Wikipedia

Saddell Castle.label: Saddell Castle
Saddell Castle.description: Saddell Castle is a 16th-century tower house on the shore of the Kilbrannan Sound near Saddell, Kintyre, Argyll and Bute, Scotland. Wikipedia

Southsea Castle.label: Southsea Castle
Southsea Castle.description: Southsea Castle is one of Henry VIII's Device Forts, also known as Henrician Castles. It was built in 1544 on the waterfront at the southern end of Portsea Island, an area that later became named Southsea after the castle. Wikipedia

Stirling Castle.label: Stirling Castle
Stirling Castle.description: Stirling Castle, located in Stirling, is one of the largest and most important castles, both historically and architecturally, in Scotland. Wikipedia

Vindolanda.label: Vindolanda
Vindolanda.description: Vindolanda was a Roman auxiliary fort just south of Hadrian's Wall in northern England. Located near the modern village of Bardon Mill, it guarded the Stanegate, the Roman road from the River Tyne to the Solway Firth. Wikipedia

Westgate, Canterbury.label: Westgate, Canterbury
Westgate, Canterbury.description: The Westgate is a medieval gatehouse in Canterbury, Kent, England. This 60-foot-high western gate of the city wall is the largest surviving city gate in England. Wikipedia

Yarmouth Castle.label: Yarmouth Castle
Yarmouth Castle.description: Yarmouth Castle is a small off-square blockhouse built by Henry VIII in 1547, to guard Yarmouth harbour on the Isle of Wight. Wikipedia

Alnarp Castle.label: Alnarp Castle
Alnarp Castle.description: Alnarp Castle is located in Alnarp, Lomma Municipality, Scania, approximately 10 km north of Malmö in southern Sweden. The original castle on the property was built in the 12th century. Wikipedia

Asen's Fortress.label: Asen's Fortress
Asen's Fortress.description: Asen's Fortress, identified by some researchers as Petrich, is a medieval fortress in the Bulgarian Rhodope Mountains, 2-3 km south of the town of Asenovgrad, on a high rocky ridge on the left bank of the Asenitsa River. Wikipedia

Codnor Castle.label: Codnor Castle
Codnor Castle.description: Codnor Castle is a ruined thirteenth-century castle in Derbyshire, England. The land around Codnor came under the jurisdiction of William Peverel after the Norman conquest. Wikipedia

Diu Fort.label: Diu Fort
Diu Fort.description: The Diu Fort, is located on the west coast of India in Diu, a Union Territory, administered by the Government of India. The fort was built by the Portuguese during their colonial rule of the Diu island. Wikipedia

Fort Drum (El Fraile Island).label: Fort Drum (El Fraile Island)
Fort Drum (El Fraile Island).description: Fort Drum (El Fraile Island), also known as the “concrete battleship,” is a heavily fortified island fortress situated at the mouth of Manila Bay in the Philippines, due south of Corregidor Island. Wikipedia

Hamina Fortress.label: Hamina Fortress
Hamina Fortress.description: Hamina Fortress is located in Finland on the coast of the Gulf of Finland and it is an integral part of the Hamina city centre. Hamina fortress is a Star fort, representing the Renaissance ideal city embodied by Palmanova city in northeastern Italy. Wikipedia

Kastellet, Copenhagen.label: Kastellet, CopenhagenKastellet
Kastellet, Copenhagen.description: Kastellet, located in Copenhagen, Denmark is one of the best preserved star fortresses in Northern Europe. It is constructed in the form of a pentagram with bastions at its corners. Wikipedia

Klis Fortress.label: Fortress of Klis
Klis Fortress.description: The Klis Fortress is a medieval fortress situated above a village bearing the same name, near the city of Split, in central Dalmatia, Croatia. Wikipedia

Ktenia (fortress).label: Ktenia
Ktenia (fortress).description: Ktenia is a ruined Roman and medieval fortress, situated 2.1 km to the north of the village of Lozarevo in Sungurlare Municipality, Burgas Province, south-eastern Bulgaria. Wikipedia

Tsepina.label: Tsepina
Tsepina.description: Tsepina was a castle and town in the western Rhodope mountains, southern Bulgaria, now in ruins. It is located at 6 km from the Dorkovo village in the north-eastern part of the Chepinska valley. Wikipedia

Underi.label: Underi
Underi.description: Underi is a fortified island near the mouth of Mumbai harbour south of Prong's Lighthouse. It is a companion fort to Khanderi and currently lies in Raigad district, Maharashtra. Wikipedia

Przemyśl Fortress.label: Przemyśl Fortress
Przemyśl Fortress.description: Przemyśl fortress was a series of fortifications constructed at Przemyśl by the Austro-Hungarian Empire from the mid 19th century until the First World War. Wikipedia

Brough Castle.label: Brough Castle
Brough Castle.description: Brough Castle is a ruined castle in the village of Brough, England. The castle was built by William Rufus around 1092 within the old Roman fort of Verterae to protect a key route through the Pennine mountains. Wikipedia

Clare Castle.label: Clare Castle
Clare Castle.description: Clare Castle is a medieval castle in the small town of Clare in Suffolk, England. Built shortly after the Norman conquest of England by Richard Fitz Gilbert, the motte and bailey castle was later improved in stone. Wikipedia

Brougham Castle.label: Brougham Castle
Brougham Castle.description: Brougham Castle is a medieval building about 2 miles south-east of Penrith, Cumbria, England. The castle was founded by Robert de Vieuxpont in the early 13th century. Wikipedia

Framlingham Castle.label: Framlingham Castle
Framlingham Castle.description: Framlingham Castle is a castle in the market town of Framlingham in Suffolk in England. An early motte and bailey or ringwork Norman castle was built on the Framlingham site by 1148, but this was ... Wikipedia

HMNB Clyde.label: HMNB Clyde
HMNB Clyde.description: Her Majesty's Naval Base Clyde is one of three operating bases in the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland for the Royal Navy. Wikipedia

Olavsvern.label: Olavsvern
Olavsvern.description: Olavsvern is a Royal Norwegian Navy auxiliary base located just outside the city of Tromsø. It is located along the European route E8 at the entrance to the Ramfjorden from the Balsfjorden. Wikipedia

Achstetten Castle.label: Achstetten Castle
Achstetten Castle.description: Achstetten Castle is a classicist mansion in the southern German municipality of Achstetten in Upper Swabia. Wikipedia

Burgistein Castle.label: Burgistein Castle
Burgistein Castle.description: Burgistein Castle is a castle in the municipality of Burgistein in the canton of Bern in Switzerland. It is a Swiss heritage site of national significance. Wikipedia

Brock Barracks.label: Brock Barracks
Brock Barracks.description: Brock Barracks is a British Army barracks in the town of Reading in the English county of Berkshire. Located on Oxford Road in the district of West Reading. The majority of the buildings and structures within Brock Barracks are Grade II listed. Wikipedia

Buxa Fort.label: Buxa Fort
Buxa Fort.description: Buxa Fort, 26°45′17.86″N 89°34′49.04″E﻿ / ﻿26.7549611°N 89.5802889°E is located at an altitude of 867 metres in the Buxa Tiger Reserve, Jalpaiguri district, West Bengal. It is located 30 kilometres from Alipurduar, the nearest town. Wikipedia

Château d'Ochsenstein.label: Château d'Ochsenstein
Château d'Ochsenstein.description: The Château d'Ochsenstein is a ruined castle located in the commune of Reinhardsmunster, in the Bas-Rhin département of France. It was home to the Ochsensteins, a powerful family from medieval Alsace. Wikipedia

Cuasso Castle.label: Cuasso Castle
Cuasso Castle.description: Known as Castelasc in Lombard local language, the Castle of Cuasso is one of the most important defensive buildings in the province of Varese and Insubria. Wikipedia

Edinburgh town walls.label: Edinburgh town walls
Edinburgh town walls.description: There have been several town walls around Edinburgh, Scotland, since the 12th century. Some form of wall probably existed from the foundation of the royal burgh in around 1125, though the first building ... Wikipedia

Fort Lowell.label: Ft. Lowell
Fort Lowell.description: Fort Lowell was a United States Army post active from 1873 to 1891 on the outskirts of Tucson, Arizona. Fort Lowell was the successor to Camp Lowell, an earlier Army installation. Wikipedia

Fort La Baye.label: Fort La Baye
Fort La Baye.description:
Fort La Baye was a French military post at La Baye, which was built in 1717, and occupied until 1760.
By 1718, there were a number of French Canadian families living in the area near the fort. Wikipedia

Kacenštajn Castle.label: Kacenštajn Castle
Kacenštajn Castle.description: Kacenštajn or Katzenštajn Castle comprises, together with the Church of St. Ursula, the old center of the village of Begunje in the Upper Carniola region of Slovenia. Wikipedia

Marine Corps Base Camp Smedley D. Butler.label: Marine Corps Base Camp Smedley D. Butler
Marine Corps Base Camp Smedley D. Butler.description: Marine Corps Base Camp Smedley D. Butler is a United States Marine Corps base located in the Japanese prefecture of Okinawa. It was named for legendary Marine Smedley D. Butler. Wikipedia

Oflag IV-B Koenigstein.label: Oflag IV-B Koenigstein
Oflag IV-B Koenigstein.description: Oflag IV-B Koenigstein was a Nazi POW camp for Allied officers during World War II. It was located in Festung Königstein near the town of Königstein in Saxony. Wikipedia

Oflag VII-B.label: Oflag VII-B
Oflag VII-B.description: Oflag VII-B was a World War II German prisoner-of-war camp for officers, located in Eichstätt, Bavaria, about 100 km north of Munich. Wikipedia

Onstaborg (Sauwerd).label: Onstaborg
Onstaborg (Sauwerd).description: Onstaborg was a borg in the northeast Netherland. It was located in Sauwerd, Groningen. The borg was founded in or before 1325 by the family Onsta. The Onsta family belonged to one of the oldest and most prominent families of the Ommelanden. Wikipedia

Ouvrage Bréhain.label: Ouvrage Bréhain
Ouvrage Bréhain.description: Ouvrage Bréhain is part of the Fortified Sector of the Crusnes of the Maginot Line, located near the community of Bréhain-la-Ville in the Meurthe-et-Moselle département of France. Bréhain is flanked by petits ouvrages Mauvais Bois and Aumetz. Wikipedia

Peterborough Castle.label: Peterborough Castle
Peterborough Castle.description: Peterborough Castle, also known as Mount Thorold and Touthill, was a medieval motte and bailey castle in Peterborough, Cambridgeshire, England. Wikipedia

Ouvrage Schoenenbourg.label: Ouvrage Schoenenbourg
Ouvrage Schoenenbourg.description: Ouvrage Schoenenbourg is a Maginot Line fortification. It is located on the territory of the communes of Hunspach, Schœnenbourg and Ingolsheim, in the French département of Bas-Rhin, forming part of the Fortified Sector of Haguenau, facing Germany. Wikipedia

RAF Deenethorpe.label: RAF Deenethorpe
RAF Deenethorpe.description: RAF Deenethorpe is a former Second World War airfield in Northamptonshire, England, about two miles east of Corby. Wikipedia

RAF Grafton Underwood.label: RAF Grafton Underwood
RAF Grafton Underwood.description: RAF Grafton Underwood is a former World War II airfield in England. The field is located 4 miles NE of Kettering in Northamptonshire. Wikipedia

Stalag II-B.label: Stalag II-B
Stalag II-B.description: Stalag II-B was a German World War II prisoner-of-war camp situated 2.4 kilometres west of the village of Hammerstein, Pomerania on the north side of the railway line. Wikipedia

Stalag XIII-D.label: Stalag XIII-D
Stalag XIII-D.description: Stalag XIII-D Nürnberg Langwasser was a German Army World War II prisoner-of-war camp built on what had been the Nazi party rally grounds in Nuremberg, northern Bavaria. Wikipedia

Tal Ashtah Air Base.label: Tal Ashtah Air Base
Tal Ashtah Air Base.description: Tal Ashtah Air Base is a former Iraqi Air Force base in the Kirkuk Governorate of Iraq. It was captured by Coalition forces during Operation Iraqi Freedom in 2003. Wikipedia

Tonopah Army Air Field.label: Tonopah Air Force Base
Tonopah Army Air Field.description: Tonopah Air Force Base is a Formerly Used Defense Site that was a Tonopah Basin military installation until shortly after it was designated an Air Force Base in 1948. Wikipedia

Fort Harmar.label: Fort Harmar
Fort Harmar.description: Fort Harmar was an early United States frontier military fort, built in pentagonal shape during 1785 at the confluence of the Ohio and Muskingum rivers, on the west side of the mouth of the Muskingum River. Wikipedia

Fort Teremba.label: Fort Teremba
Fort Teremba.description: Fort Teremba is a former fort and a prison located near Moindou in New Caledonia, which came to be set up to house prisoners and the supervisory staff. The prisoners were brought to build road network Canala-Bourail-Boulouparis. Wikipedia

Balapur Fort.label: Balapur Fort
Balapur Fort.description: Balapur Fort is a in fairly good conditionMughal fortress situated in the town of Balapur in the Akola district of India. Wikipedia

CFS St. John's.label: CFS St. John's
CFS St. John's.description: Canadian Forces Station St. John's is a Canadian Forces Station located in St. John's, Newfoundland and Labrador. Wikipedia

Dudhkundi Airfield.label: Dudhkundi Airfield
Dudhkundi Airfield.description: Dudhkundi Airfield is an abandoned airfield in India, located 12 miles SE of Jhargram, in the Paschim Medinipur district in the Indian state of West Bengal. Wikipedia

Fort de Buade.label: Fort de Buade
Fort de Buade.description: Fort de Buade was a French fort at the present site of St. Ignace in the U.S. state of Michigan. It was garrisoned between 1683 and 1701. Wikipedia

Harrisburg Air National Guard Base.label: Harrisburg Air National Guard Base
Harrisburg Air National Guard Base.description: Harrisburg Air National Guard Base is a United States Air Force base, located at Harrisburg International Airport, Pennsylvania. It is located 1.7 miles west-southwest of Middletown, Pennsylvania. Wikipedia

Kokmuiža Manor.label: Kokmuiža Manor
Kokmuiža Manor.description: Kokmuiža Manor, also called Kocēni Manor, is a manor house in the historical region of Vidzeme, in northern Latvia. It was built before 1760 in late Baroque style. The building currently houses the Kocēni primary school. Wikipedia

Lielzalve Manor.label: Lielzalve Manor
Lielzalve Manor.description: Lielzalve Manor is a two-storey manor house built in the 19th century in the historical region of Selonia, Latvia. Wikipedia

Ouvrage Sainte-Agnès.label: Ouvrage Sainte-Agnès
Ouvrage Sainte-Agnès.description: Ouvrage Sainte-Agnès was a work of the Maginot Line's Alpine extension, the Alpine Line, also called the Little Maginot Line. The fortification was built between 1932 and 1938. Wikipedia
